    "year": 2017,
    "captured": "5/26/26",
    "description": "\"The Dance\" celebrates Toronto's history of diversity as community as a literal dance, everyone holding hands in a continuous circle around the box, jumping and dancing barefoot and smiling and laughing. Bright fluorescent splashes of colour weave in and out of the dancing group to further highlight how people come together in Toronto to form a unique tapestry.",
